-- Almarai Advances Most Since February 2009 on Profit Increase, Bonus Share
-- B y   C l a u d i a   M a e d l e r
-- 2010-10-05T08:25:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/almarai-advances-most-since-february-2009-on-profit-increase-bonus-share.html
Almarai Co., the largest food
producer in Saudi Arabia, gained the most in more than a year
after third-quarter profit rose and it announced plans to issue
bonus shares.  The stock soared as much as 8.1 percent, the most since
February 2009, to 217.25 riyals. It traded at 212.75 riyals at
11:22 a.m. in Riyadh.  Net income jumped 17 percent to 424.5 million riyals. The
Riyadh-based company plans to double its capital to 2.3 billion
riyals through a bonus share issue.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Claudia Maedler in Dubai at 
